tomers_count,\n  earliest_first_transaction,\n  latest_first_transaction\nFROM monthly_customer_counts\nORDER BY\n  month DESC NULLS LAST\n -- Generated by Cortex Analyst (request_id: 89efb5e7-a566-4612-9648-bad32c1aa1dc)\n;","text":"The question is clear and I can answer it with the following SQL."},"type":"json"}],"name":"SalesSemantic","status":"success","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N7bmR2KCMVaLYuSkfDEF6y","type":"cortex_analyst_text_to_sql"},"type":"tool_result"},{"thinking":{"text":"\nPerfect! The Cortex Analyst tool understood my interpretation and generated SQL that:\n1. Identifies each customer's first transaction date\n2. Groups by month\n3. Counts the number of customers who had their first transaction in each month\n\nThe results show monthly counts from February 2025 through February 2026. The data looks complete and reasonable.\n\nNow I need to evaluate if this should be visualized:\n- Step 1: Should I visualize? Yes - this is time-series data showing new customer counts per month, which is perfect for a line chart or bar chart\n- Step 2: Is the SQL result visualization-ready? Let me check:\n  - Column names: MONTH and NEW_CUSTOMERS_COUNT are clear and appropriate ✓\n  - Aggregation level: Already aggregated by month ✓\n  - Data shape: Long format with month and count - perfect for charts ✓\n- Step 3c: The data is ready, so I should call data_to_chart directly with the SQL result tool_use_id\n\nThe tool_use_id is \"toolu_bdrk_01N7bmR2KCMVaLYuSkfDEF6y\"\n"},"type":"thinking"},{"tool_use":{"client_side_execute":false,"input":{"question":"Show the count of new customers per month based on their first transaction date as a line chart","tool_result_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N7bmR2KCMVaLYuSkfDEF6y"},"name":"data_to_chart","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JcKvK9u7PWqGVnTWMnhUZL","type":"data_to_chart"},"type":"tool_use"},{"tool_result":{"content":[{"json":{"charts":["{\"$schema\": \"https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v5.json\", \"data\": {\"values\": [{\"MONTH\": \"202