[2026-03-03T07:20:26.927Z] event=response data={"content":[{"thinking":{"text":"\nThe user wants me to count VIP customers per month based on their first_transaction_date. This is a follow-up to the previous query where we listed VIP customers with their first transaction dates.\n\nI need to:\n1. Query for VIP customers grouped by month of their first transaction\n2. Count how many VIP customers had their first transaction in each month\n3. This would benefit from visualization since it's a time series with counts\n\nLet me use the SalesSemantic tool to get the count of VIP customers by month based on first transaction date. Since I have a previous related tool result (toolu_bdrk_0166i1pvkZ4r8UYyo2xkfQfu) about VIP customers, I should reference it.\n"},"type":"thinking"},{"tool_use":{"client_side_execute":false,"input":{"has_time_column":true,"need_future_forecasting_data":false,"original_query":"can you count per month based on first_transaction_date?","previous_related_tool_result_id":"toolu_bdrk_0166i1pvkZ4r8UYyo2xkfQfu","query":"count of VIP customers per month based on their first transaction date (the earliest created_at timestamp for each customer)"},"name":"SalesSemantic","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01U86Snfe9VzVBdZ5e2Gu8Ai","type":"cortex_analyst_text_to_sql"},"type":"tool_use"},{"tool_result":{"content":[{"json":{"query_id":"01c2c698-0001-57c3-0000-920d002dffca","result_set":{"data":[["2026-02-01 00:00:00.000","846","2026-02-07 23:52:47.775","2026-02-20 09:22:25.999","846"]],"resultSetMetaData":{"format":"jsonv2","numRows":1,"partition":0,"partitionInfo":[{"rowCount":1,"uncompressedSize":102}],"rowType":[{"length":0,"name":"MONTH","nullable":true,"precision":0,"scale":9,"type":"timestamp_tz"},{"length":0,"name":"VIP_CUSTOMER_COUNT","nullable":false,"precision":18,"scale":0,"type":"fixed"},{"length":0,"name":"EARLIEST_FIRST_TRANSACTION","nullable":true,"precision":0,"scale":9,"type":"timestamp_tz"},{"length":0,"name":"LATEST_FIRST_TRANSACTION","nullable":true,"precision":0,"scale":9,"type":"timestamp_tz"},{"length":0,"name":"UNIQUE_VIP_CUSTOMERS","nullable":false,"precision":18,"scale":0,"type":"fixed"}]},"statementHandle":"01c2c698-0001-57c3-0000-920d002dffca"},"sql":"WITH __tbl_sales AS (\n  SELECT\n    customer_name,\n    is_vip_customer,\n    created_at\n  FROM DEVELOPMENT.BRONZE.TBL_SALES\n), customer_first_transaction AS (\n  SELECT\n    customer_name,\n    is_vip_customer,\n    MIN(created_at) AS first_transaction_date\n  FROM __tbl_sales\n  WHERE\n    created_at \u003c= CURRENT_TIMESTAMP()\n  GROUP BY\n    customer_name,\n    is_vip_customer\n), vip_customers_by_month AS (\n  SELECT\n    DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', first_transaction_date) AS month,\n    COUNT(*) AS vip_customer_count,\n    MIN(first_transaction_date) AS earliest_first_transaction,\n    MAX(first_transaction_date) AS latest_first_transaction,\n    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_name) AS unique_vip_customers\n  FROM customer_first_transaction\n  WHERE\n    is_vip_customer = TRUE\n  GROUP BY\n    DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', first_transaction_date)\n)\nSELECT\n  month,\n  vip_customer_count,\n  earliest_first_transaction,\n  latest_first_transaction,\n  unique_vip_customers\nFROM vip_customers_by_month\nORDER BY\n  month DESC NULLS LAST\n -- Generated by Cortex Analyst (request_id: 5f03e1cb-c1cf-4a34-a33d-184ca5e85489)\n;","text":"The question is clear and I can answer it with the following SQL."},"type":"json"}],"name":"SalesSemantic","status":"success","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01U86Snfe9VzVBdZ5e2Gu8Ai","type":"cortex_analyst_text_to_sql"},"type":"tool_result"},{"thinking":{"text":"\nI received the SQL results showing VIP customer counts by month. The data shows:\n- Month: February 2026\n- VIP Customer Count: 846\n- Earliest first transaction: 2026-02-07\n- Latest first transaction: 2026-02-20\n- Unique VIP customers: 846\n\nSo all 846 VIP customers had their first transaction in February 2026. This means there's only one month of data, so a time series chart wouldn't be very meaningful here since there's only a single data point.\n\nShould I generate a chart?\n- Step 1: Does this contain numerical/quantitative data suitable for visualization? Yes, it has a count.\n- Step 2: Is the data visualization-ready? Yes, it has month and count.\n- However, with only 1 data point (1 month), a chart would not add much value. A line or bar chart with a single point isn't very informative.\n- Decision: Skip chart generation. A single data point doesn't benefit from visualization - the table/text answer is more appropriate.\n\nI have sufficient information to answer the question.\n"},"type":"thinking"},{"text":"All 846 VIP customers had their first transaction in **February 2026**:\n\n- **Month**: February 2026\n- **VIP Customer Count**: 846\n- **First Transaction Date Range**: February 7, 2026 to February 20, 2026\n\nSince all VIP customers in the dataset joined during February 2026, there is only one month of data available.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"run_id":"9571696-2450330133","usage":{"tokens_consumed":[{"context_window":200000,"input_tokens":{"cache_read":57979,"cache_write":25903,"total":83889,"uncached":7},"model_name":"claude-sonnet-4-5","output_tokens":{"total":732}}]}},"role":"assistant","schema_version":"v2","sequence_number":191}
